obile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534624\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 16, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zuo1665702942919.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zuo1665702942919.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zuo1665702942919.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zuo1665702942919\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n Environment Considerations for Microsoft SQL Server \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"zuo1665702942919__environment_considerations_for_microsoft_sql_server_154552\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The MSS connector makes use of ODBC to connect to Microsoft SQL Server, and requires the correct the ODBC Driver for SQL Server or the SQL Server Native Client version to be installed on the client machine.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zuo1665702942919__p_d51596e1_d51597e1_d51598e1\">For versions of the Microsoft SQL Server supported by\n         Uniface, see the <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://community.rocketsoftware.com/rocket-uniface-forum-home-20/uniface-product-availability-information-18191\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Platform Availability Matrix</a>. For the corresponding version of\n         the Microsoft ODBC Driver, consult the Microsoft documentation (<a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us%2Flibrary%2Fjj730315.aspx\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/jj730315.aspx</a>).</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zuo1665702942919__topic_d33927e1_d33928e1_d33929e1_d33930e1_d33931e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d588587e64\">\n                        \n Permissions\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zuo1665702942919__p_d51605e1_d51606e1_d51607e1\">For each database you access, you must have select permission on certain system tables. However, database owners can control the permissions on the system tables in their own databases.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"zuo1665702942919__table_d4784e1_d4785e1_d4786e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\"> for Which Users Must Have select Permission</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zuo1665702942919__table_d4784e1_d4785e1_d4786e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Table</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zuo1665702942919__table_d4784e1_d4785e1_d4786e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Purpose</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zuo1665702942919__table_d4784e1_d4785e1_d4786e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">sysusers</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zuo1665702942919__table_d4784e1_d4785e1_d4786e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Used to check the existence of stored procedures for a specific user.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zuo1665702942919__table_d4784e1_d4785e1_d4786e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">sysobjects</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zuo1665702942919__table_d4784e1_d4785e1_d4786e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Used to check the existence of stored procedures.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zuo1665702942919__topic_d33932e1_d33933e1_d33934e1_d33935e1_d33936e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d588587e143\">\n                        \n Network Considerations\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zuo1665702942919__p_d51611e1_d51612e1_d51613e1\">Microsoft SQL Server always uses a network for accessing the server, even if the server is on the local machine. Accessing servers on other machines is completely transparent for Uniface. For more information on server administration, see the Microsoft SQL Server documentation.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zuo1665702942919__p_d51614e1_d51615e1_d51616e1\">The Uniface Server is supported. This also provides transparent network connectivity.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534624\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534624\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Environment Considerations for Microsoft SQL Server Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 16, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Environment Considerations for Microsoft SQL Server The MSS connector makes use of ODBC to connect to Microsoft SQL Server, and requires the correct the ODBC Driver for SQL Server or the SQL Server Native Client version to be installed on the client machine. For versions of the Microsoft SQL Server supported by Uniface, see the Platform Availability Matrix . For the corresponding version of the Microsoft ODBC Driver, consult the Microsoft documentation ( https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/jj730315.aspx ). Permissions For each database you access, you must have select permission on certain system tables. However, database owners can control the permissions on the system tables in their own databases. Table 1. for Which Users Must Have select Permission Table Purpose sysusers Used to check the existence of stored procedures for a specific user. sysobjects Used to check the existence of stored procedures. Network Considerations Microsoft SQL Server always uses a network for accessing the server, even if the server is on the local machine. Accessing servers on other machines is completely transparent for Uniface. For more information on server administration, see the Microsoft SQL Server documentation. The Uniface Server is supported. This also provides transparent network connectivity. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}